#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Armor_00"
msgid ""
"Armor Sets<1.ra>Wearing the top, bottom, and headwear from the same set "
"can earn\n"
"you some bonus effects."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_00"
msgid ""
"Collecting Ingredients<1.ra>There are many more ingredients than those "
"used for cooking food.\n"
"Collect and experiment with different ingredients to make all sorts\n"
"of things!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_01"
msgid ""
"Cooking Secrets<1.ra>Using more of an effect-imparting ingredient when "
"cooking will\n"
"increase that effect in the resulting dish."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_02"
msgid ""
"Monster Ingredients<1.ra>If you combine monster parts dropped by fallen "
"foes in a cooking pot\n"
"with things like lizards and butterflies, you can create elixirs with\n"
"special effects."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_03"
msgid ""
"Roasting Ingredients<1.ra>Throw ingredients like mushrooms or fish "
"directly into a fire to roast \n"
"them and up their health benefits. Keep in mind that roasting an\n"
"ingredient won't activate its potential special effect."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_04"
msgid ""
"Fairy Effects<1.ra>If you keep a fairy in your pouch, it will "
"automatically restore some\n"
"hearts when you fall in battle."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_05"
msgid ""
"Gems<1.ra>The gems that sometimes drop when you break ore deposits fetch\n"
"a high price when sold."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_06"
msgid ""
"Cooking Pots<1.ra>Cook up some wild cuisine by throwing together some "
"ingredients\n"
"and seeing what happens. You can't cook with an unlit pot."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_07"
msgid ""
"Cutting Grass<1.ra>Wildlife taking shelter in the grass will sometimes "
"jump out when you\n"
"cut down their hiding place."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_08"
msgid ""
"No Stone Unturned<1.ra>Wildlife taking shelter under a rock will "
"sometimes jump out when you\n"
"lift up their hiding place."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_09"
msgid ""
"Octo Balloon<1.ra>When inflated, this sac obtained from defeating "
"Octoroks is\n"
"extremely buoyant. Place one near something you want to lift\n"
"to make it float into the air."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_10"
msgid ""
"Fairy Effects<1.ra>If you have a fairy help you cook, the tonic you "
"produce together\n"
"restores a great deal of hearts."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_11"
msgid ""
"Scorching Climates<1.ra>In the extreme heat of volcanic regions, "
"ingredients will cook simply\n"
"by placing them on the ground. Use this to your advantage to\n"
"prepare meals on the go."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_12"
msgid ""
"Freezing Climates<1.ra>Some ingredients will freeze if submerged in ice-"
"cold water or when\n"
"left out in frigid regions. There are a few ingredients that taste\n"
"even better frozen."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_13"
msgid ""
"Luring Fish<1.ra>Tossing ingredients that serve as bait near fish in the "
"water will\n"
"attract them. Different bait works on different kinds of fish."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_14"
msgid ""
"What's That, Pooch?<1.ra>If you befriend a dog, it may lead you to "
"something interesting."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_15"
msgid ""
"Ingredient Effects<1.ra>Certain ingredients give elixirs or dishes "
"special properties.\n"
"But don't get greedy: ingredients with different effects will\n"
"cancel each other out."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Material_16"
msgid ""
"Ingredient Effects<1.ra>You can only enjoy one effect from a dish or "
"elixir at any given time.\n"
"If you're relying on an active effect, be careful not to cancel it\n"
"by eating something with a new effect."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Weapon_00"
msgid ""
"Where's the Fire?<1.ra>When a wooden weapon or shield catches fire, you "
"can extinguish\n"
"it by unequipping the burning item."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Weapon_01"
msgid ""
"Weapon Durability<1.ra>Durability varies with every weapon. Always be "
"aware of the condition\n"
"of your equipment. A weapon breaking at the wrong time is never\n"
"a good thing."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
#. 2: icon
msgctxt "Weapon_02"
msgid ""
"Throwing Weapons<1.ra>If your weapon is close to breaking, try throwing "
"it at an enemy\n"
"using <2.ic>. It will double your damage if it hits!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Weapon_03"
msgid ""
"Special Bows<1.ra>A few bows fire multiple arrows at once. They offer "
"several times\n"
"the power of normal bows, while strangely only consuming one\n"
"arrow at a time."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Weapon_04"
msgid ""
"More Than a Weapon<1.ra>Metal weapons create sparks that can be used to "
"light a fire.\n"
"Furthermore, if you set a wooden weapon on fire, it can be\n"
"used as a torch."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
#. 2: icon
msgctxt "Weapon_06"
msgid ""
"Boomerangs<1.ra>Throw a boomerang with <2.ic>, and it will fly in a large"
" arc before\n"
"returning to you. What goes around comes around!"
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Weapon_07"
msgid ""
"Weapon Bonuses<1.ra>Some weapons you'll come across have special "
"properties that set\n"
"them apart from others of their class, such as superior durability or\n"
"above-average attack power."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
msgctxt "Weapon_08"
msgid ""
"Critical Hit<1.ra>When using a weapon with this bonus, the last hit in a "
"series of\n"
"attacks will deal double the damage."
msgstr ""

#. 1: raw
#. 2: icon
msgctxt "Weapon_09"
msgid ""
"Master Sword<1.ra>When your hearts are full, you can fire a beam from the"
" sword\n"
"with <2.ic>. The more Heart Containers you have, the further the\n"
"beam's range."
msgstr ""

